precondition:
1. jenkins is up

2. argocd is up
kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8081:80
admin/123456

quick start:
kubectl apply -f argocd/my-devops-helm-app-application.yaml
kubectl port-forward -n default svc/my-devops-helm-app-service 5000:5000

kubectl delete -f argocd/my-devops-helm-app-application.yaml
note: delete application only delete the application resource. to delete all related resource:
kubectl get deployment
kubectl get rs
kubectl get pod
kubectl get service
kubectl delete deployment my-devops-helm-app
kubectl delete service my-devops-helm-app-service


files except helm folder are copied from project my-devops-demo

helm folder create step:
1. mkdir helm
2. cd helm
3. helm create my-devops-helm-app (create helm structure, then manually
delete unwanted files, update file content)
4. cd ..
5. helm template my-devops-helm-app helm/my-devops-helm-app (remder template locally.
you can also try
helm template dev helm/my-app
helm template prod helm/my-app)
